    <h1>Our language: loss and revival.</h1>
    <p class="lead">The treaty is more than land and money. It is also the language that carries who we are. Anishinaabemowin, in our own Nishnaabemwin dialect of the Lake Huron shore and Manitoulin, is under real strain, and the 21 nations are working together to bring it back.</p>
